THE Willowvale Regional Magistrate Court sentenced rapist Pumezo Sikhahlane (23) to 25 years imprison on Tuesday. He was convicted of raping an eleven 11-year-old girl. "The accused met the victim on 24 August 2017 at about
10:00 at Hlakothi Locality, Ntsimbakazi Village, Willowvale. He did not say
anything but dragged the victim to his home where undressed and raped
her," Police spokesperson Capt Jackson Manatha said. A case of rape was then opened at Willowvale Police Station. "The case was handed over to Butterworth Family
Violence, Child Protection and Sexual Offences Unit (FCS) for
investigation." The accused was traced and arrested, and he was charged with
rape. Eastern Cape Police Provincial Commissioner, Lieutenant
General Liziwe Ntshinga condemned violence and rape of both children and women. "She welcomed the hefty sentence handed to the accused
as it will serve as a deterrent to all other men who still ponder of sexual
abusing women and children."